# Caching


a resource in finland may take 100ms to reach user in italy, but 4 sec to mexico

use caching or CDN (content delivery network)

caching is used to improve performance by storing a copy of data in a temporary storage (cache)

cache example
1) web browser stores on local machine
http cache related headers = cache-control

2) server caching - cache that stores on a server
eg: redis
server checks data from server before asking from db

3) database caching
similar with server caching 
eg redis, memchace

4) CDN caching
server that are located in each continent
when user request a file, it is redirect to the nearest CDN server.
stores JS, CSS, HTML files